# User Feature Jurisdiction Source

For authenticated `/v1/*` user feature routes, data access must use `request.account.jurisdiction_id`.

## Required

```typescript
if (!request.account) {
   throw new ForbiddenException();
}
const jurisdiction_id = request.account.jurisdiction_id;
await this.entities.widgetManager.getById(jurisdiction_id, input.widget_id);
```

## Avoid

```typescript
await this.entities.widgetManager.getById(input.jurisdiction_id, input.widget_id);
```

Caller-provided jurisdiction is valid for admin routes, federation routes, public legal/bootstrap flows, webhooks, or documented cross-jurisdiction hydration. For user-owned data, the authenticated account is the source of truth.
